Sentencas: Detailed comparisons of fluid flow, concentration, and electric fields between the planar solid oxide fuel cell (planar SOFC) and the monoblock-layer-built solid oxide fuel cell (MOLB-type SOFC) are made in the present study.
Titulo: Detailed characteristic comparison between planar and MOLB-type SOFCs

Sentencas: A multi-physics model is developed to simulate the SOFCs of different geometries.
Titulo: Detailed characteristic comparison between planar and MOLB-type SOFCs

Sentencas: The model couples the electrochemical kinetics with the fluid dynamics and multi-component species transport.
Titulo: Detailed characteristic comparison between planar and MOLB-type SOFCs

Sentencas: Darcy's law governs the flow momentum in the porous electrodes.
Titulo: Detailed characteristic comparison between planar and MOLB-type SOFCs

Sentencas: The Bruggman model depicts the diffusion of reactant species within the electrodes.
Titulo: Detailed characteristic comparison between planar and MOLB-type SOFCs

Sentencas: The electrochemical kinetics and the species transport on the electrode surfaces is connected by the Butler-Volmer equation.
Titulo: Detailed characteristic comparison between planar and MOLB-type SOFCs

Sentencas: Results show that the MOLB-type SOFC has a higher fuel/oxidant utilization than the planar SOFC.
Titulo: Detailed characteristic comparison between planar and MOLB-type SOFCs

Sentencas: The high utilization of the fuel/oxidant reflects the high current through the SOFC.
Titulo: Detailed characteristic comparison between planar and MOLB-type SOFCs
